events.name: New York Knicks at Orlando Magic

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner had 32 points and nine rebounds, Paolo Banchero added 29 points and 10 rebounds and the Orlando Magic held off the New York Knicks 117-108 on Friday night
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner, Paolo Banchero help Magic beat Knicks 117-108

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 26 points, Deni Avdija had 21 points, 13 rebounds and six assists, and the Washington Wizards beat the Brooklyn Nets 110-104 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Avdija, Kuzma lead Wizards to 110-104 victory over the Nets

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 26 of his 31 points after halftime and the Sacramento Kings rallied from a 23-point, first-quarter deficit to beat the Atlanta Hawks 117-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: De'Aaron Fox's big second half leads Kings to 117-110 come-from-behind win over Hawks

headlines.description: — Jaylen Brown returned from a one-game absence to score 31 points and fed Luke Kornet for the tiebreaking basket as the Boston Celtics beat the Toronto Raptors 120-118 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 31 points, sets up Kornet's tiebreaking basket as Celtics beat Raptors 120-118

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points and 16 rebounds, Damian Lillard scored 24 of his 31 points in the second half, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 119-111 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis Antetokounmpo scores 34, leads Bucks to a 119-111 win over the Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey had 42 points and the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers outlasted the Houston Rockets 131-127 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyrese Maxey scores 42 points, short-handed 76ers outlast Rockets 131-127

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 40 points, 17 in the decisive third quarter, and the Oklahoma City Thunder overcame another efficient shooting game from Nikola Jokic to beat the Denver Nuggets 119-93 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40, Thunder snap Nuggets' 6-game win streak with 119-93 victory

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 35 points and the Phoenix Suns, with Bradley Beal back on the court, beat Charlotte 133-119 on Friday night to hand the Hornets their 10th consecutive loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 35 points, Beal returns to help Suns hand Hornets 10th straight loss, 133-119

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Jerami Grant and Malcolm Brogdon each scored 27 points and the Portland Trail Blazers took advantage of San Antonio rookie star Victor Wembanyama’s absence to beat the Spurs 134-128 on Friday night for a split in the two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Trail Blazers beat Spurs 134-128 to split 2-game set in Portland

headlines.description: — What a difference a month makes for James Harden and the Los Angeles Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Harden help Clippers close successful December with 117-106 win over Grizzlies
